Citation.sTitle: Studies on the Interactions of Saccharides and Methyl Glycosides with Lithium Chloride in Aqueous Solutions at (288.15 to 318.15) K
Citation.sAbstract: Standard partial molar volumes, V2o, at infinite dilution and viscosity B-coefficients (employing the Jones Dole equation) have been calculated from the respective density and efflux time measurements for various solutes (mono-, di-, and trisaccharides, and their derivatives; methyl glycosides) in aqueous solutions of lithium chloride of (0.5, 1.0, 2.0, and 3.0) mol*kg 1 at temperatures of (288.15 to 318.15) K. The corresponding transfer parameters, interaction coefficients, partial molar expansibilities, and dB/dT coefficients have been evaluated and discussed in terms of the solute solvent and solute cosolute interactions. The results have been compared for the solutes studied in the presence of (1:1 and 1:2/2:1) electrolytes to arrive at the conclusions of how these solutes interact with the mono- and divalent cations.
